# AI Context Configuration - docs/

## Directory Purpose
Canonical documentation - architecture, guides, implementation records, and ADRs.

## AI Indexing Priority
PRIORITY: MEDIUM
Reference documentation - index on request or for specific documentation tasks.

## Scope
DOCUMENTATION - Living documentation that evolves with the system.

## Key Components
- Architecture documents (ARCHITECTURE.md, etc.)
- Implementation summaries (PHASE_*_COMPLETE.md)
- Configuration guides
- Refactor mapping (SECTION_REFACTOR_MAPPING.md)
- CI standards (CI_PATH_STANDARDS.md)

## Content Standards
- One H1 per file
- Sentence-case headings
- ~100 char line wrapping
- Include metadata headers (purpose, last updated, related docs)

## When to Use This Section
- Understanding system architecture
- Finding implementation history
- Learning conventions and standards
- Navigating refactored code paths

## Related Sections
- meta/ - Planning documents
- AGENTS.md - Coding guidelines
- README.md - Main overview
- DIRECTORY_GUIDE.md - Navigation guide

## AI Usage Notes
- Use for reference and understanding
- Do not modify unless updating documentation
- Cross-reference with code when needed
- Check for staleness (last updated dates)

## Exclude from Context
- .index/ (generated files)
- __pycache__/
